reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 28, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Perfect for DIY
reviews.reviewText: These were perfect for what I was needing and looking for. I put together first aid survival kids for my kids and a couple friends and gave them as a gift for Christmas. Loved that it actually has first aid on the front with the symbol - no need to second guess what bag your grabbing. Had enough pockets to sort the basics. Quality seems a bit on the cheap side but they are holding up well and have no complaints. Would order again and just might be in the near future.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 1, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Good size for everyday carry, but annoying design flaws
reviews.reviewText: For the price, I'm pretty happy with these. I might have ordered something different for slightly more money, though, if I had known the following design flaws:• 𝗧𝗵𝗲 𝘁𝘄𝗼 𝗼𝘃𝗲𝗿𝗹𝗮𝗽𝗽𝗶𝗻𝗴 𝗺𝗲𝘀𝗵 𝗽𝗼𝗰𝗸𝗲𝘁𝘀 𝗼𝗻 𝘁𝗵𝗲 𝗶𝗻𝘀𝗶𝗱𝗲 𝗮𝗿𝗲 𝘃𝗲𝗿𝘆 "𝘀𝗻𝗮𝗴𝗴𝘆."These make it VERY annoying to get things in and out if they have corners – such as the packaging on bandaids, and tubes of Neosporin. These kinds of items are exactly what you're supposed to put in these pouches, and they snag like crazy.• 𝗘𝘅𝗰𝗲𝘀𝘀 𝗺𝗮𝘁𝗲𝗿𝗶𝗮𝗹 𝗶𝗻𝘀𝗶𝗱𝗲 𝗮𝗿𝗼𝘂𝗻𝗱 𝘁𝗵𝗲 𝟯 𝗲𝗱𝗴𝗲𝘀 𝘄𝗵𝗲𝗿𝗲 𝘁𝗵𝗲 𝘇𝗶𝗽𝗽𝗲𝗿 𝗼𝗽𝗲𝗻𝘀/𝗰𝗹𝗼𝘀𝗲𝘀 𝘁𝗵𝗲 𝗽𝗼𝘂𝗰𝗵.It's very easy for the zipper to snag and jam on this material, especially when opening the pouch. Hopefully you're only using these pouches for everyday "ouchies" like when your kid scrapes his knee at the park, and not life-saving emergencies. In the latter case, having a zipper jam when you're trying to open this is NOT what you want to have happen. (I guess in that case you could just rely on adrenaline and break the heck out of the zipper to bust the pouch open.)That said, these are decent pouches overall and I'm satisfied with them for my purposes. They have enough pockets inside, and they're the right size to hold the basics you'd want to have for everyday use. I filled each of mine with all the following items:• 1 pouch of BleedStop powder• 5 packs of single-use Neosporin• 3 tubes of single-use eye drops• 3 packs of single-use antiseptic wipes• 5 each of small, medium, and large bandages• 3 extra large bandages• 3 knuckle bandagesThere's definitely room if I wanted to add a few more items like gauze or a pair of vinyl gloves.

reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars DIY First Aid Kit
reviews.reviewText: Perfect for cub scouts to put together their own first aid kit. They love that there are two colors so siblings can have different ones. Purchased twice as more boys joined. Very happy with my purchase.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 3, 2023
reviews.reviewText: As another reviewer said (and I wish I'd read their comments before buying these!!) the pouches have a GREAT capacity but a MAJOR design flaw. The excess fabric near the zipper makes it catch every single time I've opened it. As the other review said, not a big deal if this is for everyday "ouches", but I bought these specifically for life-threatening bleeding situations because I have a prosthetic heart valve and am on 2 blood thinners, but I am a very active 20-something. I would need access to the BleedStop and kaolin bandages inside IMMEDIATELY. Overall these are cheaply made, but again, very good capacity. Just be advised to look for another option if you were to rely on anything in this pouch to save a life, like epi pens.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 29, 2023
reviews.reviewText: I purchased these to make little hangover kits for my daughter and her friends while in Vegas celebrating a 21st birthday. I wanted to fill them with travel size items, such as hair ties, hand sanitizer, face hydrating mask, Advil, mini lotion, tums etc….1 out of the 4 was properly made. The others were so miss shaped that they weren’t rectangles. They couldn’t be zipped up, the pockets inside were not sewn correctly. They were terrible. Basically not useable. We were leaving the next day so I didn’t have time to replace them through Amazon. I found some others locally, but was disappointed with what this store had to offer. Such a disappointment. I guess you get what you pay for.

reviews.reviewText: Traveled with my elderly parents and aunt this winter. Labeled each bag with their name and Used these to hold and manage each ones medications (I had seperated into small medicine bags I also purchased prior to putting in bag ) their covid 19 immunization cards, medication list, Drs names and phone numbers and insurance cards.
